title: Auckland train services disrupted by death
text:
Auckland train services disrupted by death 
Monday 20 Jul 2015 1:16 p.m. 
A train station in Auckland has been closed after a person has died. (3 News) 
A train station in Auckland has been closed after a person fell to their death from a neighbouring building onto the train tracks below. 
Police are examining the scene where the incident happened today at around 12:20pm in Newmarket. 
All train lines in and out of the station are currently closed as a result. 
Western lines remain open as they bypass Newmarket until the lines have reopened. 
Emergency services are also at the scene. 
3 News
